external_knowledge:
- "Sailed above the average wave" metaphorically refers to having an intent score greater than the average;
- "Intent over the past month" refers to the average intent score calculated over the last 30 days;
- "Staying within the recent horizon of the last 30 days" means the interactions must have occurred within the last 30 days.

sql:
SELECT research_project_id
FROM interactions
WHERE power_dynamics_score > 0.5 AND size != 'Small';

SELECT project_name
FROM research_projects
WHERE project_id = 0;

SELECT interaction_id, intent_score
FROM interactions
WHERE size = 'Large' AND power_dynamics_score = 0;

SELECT i.size, er.reaction_id, er.reaction_duration
FROM interactions i
JOIN emotional_reactions er ON i.interaction_id = er.interaction_id
WHERE i.intent_score > (
  SELECT AVG(intent_score) FROM interactions
);

external_knowledge:
- "garden of interactions" metaphorically refers to the dataset containing interaction records;
- "blossoms" are the detailed attributes such as size, intent, and scores;
- "tender caress of human touch" is a metaphor for user interactions or the user count;
- "ratio of interaction's soul to the multitude of its visitors" refers to the ratio of average scores to the total number of distinct users.
